KW  - Labor migration
KW  - Political freedom
KW  - Economic incentives
KW  - Africa
AB  - Policy reforms in developing countries often address in isolation either an economic or a political problem. This study examines the interaction between political institutions and responses of labor migration to economic incentives. Migration data from thirty two African countries were used to quantify the statistical relationships between political institutions and labor migration out of agriculture. Regression results indicate that the presence of political freedoms and civil liberties increases the responsiveness of labor migration to economic incentives.
