KW  - Debt overhang problem
KW  - Solvency condition
KW  - Unit root
KW  - Cointegration
AB  - This paper investigates whether the Heavily Indebted Countries (HICs), in consideration of their external debt repayments, remain solvent. Direct tests of the solvency condition derived from the usual intertemporal budget constraints shed light on the sustainability of their current policies. The findings are twofold. First, the HICs seem to have a debt overhang problem. Second, in East and Southeast Asian countries except Philippines, the solvency conditions are satisfied. These results give a rationale for the debt reduction plan (a.k.a. the Brady Plan) and the empirical support of the debt overhang hypothesis.
ER  - 

