KW  - Foreign capital
KW  - Income inequality
KW  - Unemployment
KW  - Free trade
KW  - Brecher-Alejandro proposition
AB  - The effects of an inflow of foreign capital on social welfare are analysed in a mobile-capital, Harris-Todaro economy, in which all income earned by foreign capital is repatriated, and in which there is no tariff. We consider the welfare measure of Sen (1974) which incorporates the Gini-coefficient of the income distribution. It is shown that an inflow of foreign capital worsens the income distribution and lowers social welfare according to Sen's measure, even in the absence of a tariff, if the manufacturing sector is capital-intensive relative to the agricultural sector in employment-adjusted terms.
